.TH NEXUS 1 "2026-07-16" "0.1.0" "Nexus Framework CLI"
.SH NAME
nexus \- scaffold native desktop and Android apps from bundled templates
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B nexus generate
\fI--type\fR \fIdesktop\fR|\fIandroid\fR \fI--name\fR \fINAME\fR [\fIoptions\fR]
.br
.B nexus version
.br
.B nexus help
.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBnexus\fR is the headless CLI for the Nexus Framework. It reads a
\fBblueprint.json\fR node graph, applies the matching template
(\fIdesktop-app\fR or \fIandroid-app\fR), substitutes placeholders, and
emits a complete native project tree under
\fBbuilds/framework/\fR\fI{name}\fR\fB/\fR.

The generated project uses a C++20 MVC architecture with SDL3, Dear ImGui,
sol2 (Lua), pybind11 (Python), and an optional TS/XHTML DSL.  Android
builds use Zig JNI + Chaquopy instead of pybind11.

All native builds are orchestrated by Zig 0.14.  CMake, Ninja, the NDK,
and Djinni have been fully removed from both templates.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B generate
Scaffold a project from bundled templates.  See OPTIONS below.
.TP
.B version
Print the CLI version and exit.
.TP
.B help
Display usage information (same as \fB\-\-help\fR or \fB\-h\fR).
.SH GENERATE OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-type\fR \fIdesktop\fR|\fIandroid\fR
App template to use.  Required.
.RS
.TP
\(bu \fIdesktop\fR \(em SDL3 + ImGui + pybind11 native binary
.TP
\(bu \fIandroid\fR \(em SDL3/GLES + Chaquopy + Zig JNI bridge APK
.RE
.TP
\fB\-\-name\fR \fINAME\fR
Project name.  Used as the output directory name, C++ namespace, and
window title (unless overridden).  Required.
.TP
\fB\-\-output\fR \fIPATH\fR
Output directory.  Default:
\fBbuilds/framework/\fR\fI{name}\fR
.TP
\fB\-\-window\-title\fR \fITITLE\fR
Override the window title.  Default:
\fI{name}\fR \- built with The Nexus Framework
.TP
\fB\-\-cpp\-standard\fR \fIN\fR
C++ language standard.  Default: 20.  Currently only 20 is supported.
.TP
\fB\-\-license\fR \fILICENSE\fR
SPDX license identifier.  Default: Apache-2.0.
.TP
\fB\-\-script\-protection\fR \fIbool\fR
Encrypt Lua and Python asset packs (lua.dat, python.dat).  Default: true.
Set to false to emit plaintext scripts for debugging.
.TP
\fB\-\-dry\-run\fR
Preview generated file paths and template substitutions without writing
anything to disk.  Useful for debugging blueprint.json graphs.
.TP
\fB\-\-force\fR
Overwrite the output directory if it already exists and is non-empty.
Without this flag, the command fails if the output directory exists.
.TP
\fB\-\-verbose\fR
Enable verbose logging from the template engine, including every
placeholder substitution.  Implied by $DEBUG environment variable.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Preview a desktop project (no files written):
.RS
nexus generate \-\-type desktop \-\-name PlotterApp \-\-dry-run
.RE
.TP
Generate an Android project to a custom path:
.RS
nexus generate \-\-type android \-\-name MyApp \-\-output builds/framework/MyApp
.RE
.TP
Generate a desktop project with encryption disabled:
.RS
nexus generate \-\-type desktop \-\-name DebugApp \-\-script-protection false
.RE
.SH INVOCATION
The CLI is distributed as a Gradle application.  Invoke it from the
repository root:
.PP
.RS
./gradlew :cli:run \-\-args="\fIarguments\fR"
.RE
.PP
The Gradle wrapper bootstraps the JDK 26 toolchain automatically.
There is no standalone \fBnexus\fR binary; the man page documents the
command-line contract that the Gradle task implements.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
0
Success.
.TP
1
Missing required flag, invalid argument, or generation failure.
.SH FILES
.TP
\fBtemplate/desktop-app/\fR
Desktop template skeleton (build.zig, C++ sources, Lua/Python stubs).
.TP
\fBtemplate/android-app/\fR
Android template skeleton (Gradle project, Zig JNI, Chaquopy config).
.TP
\fBtemplate/shared/\fR
Shared runtime modules, DSL definitions, and themes.
.TP
\fBbuilds/framework/\fR\fI{name}\fR\fB/\fR
Default output directory for generated projects.
.TP
\fBbuilds/client/\fR
Packaged Compose Desktop distributions and OS installers.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
\fBZIG_HOME\fR
Path to Zig 0.14.0 installation (set by \fBmisc/client-setup/env.sh\fR).
.TP
\fBANDROID_NDK\fR
Required when building the generated Android project's native .so.
.TP
\fBDEBUG\fR
If set, enables verbose template engine logging (same as \fB\-\-verbose\fR).
.SH STANDARDS
The generated projects conform to Apache 2.0 licensing.  C++20 modules
follow the standard \fB.cppm\fR convention.  Zig builds use the 0.14.x
stable release channel.
.SH REPORTING BUGS
File issues at https://github.com/anomalyco/opencode/issues
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR gradle (1),
.BR zig (1),
.BR cmake (1) \-
legacy, no longer used by Nexus
